h6401.definition: from {{h6400}}; slicing; Pilcha, an Israelite; Pilcha.

h6403.definition: a primitive root; to slip out, i.e. escape; causatively, to deliver; calve, carry away safe, deliver, (cause to) escape.

h6404.definition: from {{h6403}}; escape; Pelet, the name of two Israelites; Pelet. See also {{h1046}}.

h6406.definition: from {{h6403}}; delivered; Palti, the name of two Israelites; Palti, Phalti.

h6407.definition: patronymically from {{h6406}}; a Paltite or descendant of Palti; Paltite.

h6409.definition: from the same as {{h6404}} and {{h410}}; deliverance of God; Paltiel, the name of two Israelites; Paltiel, Phaltiel.

h6410.definition: or פְּלַטְיָהוּ; from {{h6403}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has delivered; Pelatjah, the name of four Israelites; Pelatiah.

h6411.definition: or פְּלָאיָה; from {{h6381}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has distinguished; Pelajah, the name of three Israelites; Pelaiah.

h6412.definition: or פָּלֵיט; or פָּלֵט; from {{h6403}}; a refugee; (that have) escape(-d, -th), fugitive.

h6413.definition: or פְּלֵטָה; feminine of {{h6412}}; deliverance; concretely, an escaped portion; deliverance, (that is) escape(-d), remnant.

h6418.definition: from an unused root meaning to be round; a circuit (i.e. district); also a spindle (as whirled); hence, a crutch; (di-) staff, participle

h6419.definition: a primitive root; to judge (officially or mentally); by extension, to intercede, pray; intreat, judge(-ment), (make) pray(-er, -ing), make supplication.

h6420.definition: from {{h6419}}; judge; Palal, an Israelite; Palal.

h6421.definition: from {{h6419}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has judged; Pelaljah, an Israelite; Pelaliah.

h6422.definition: probably for {{h6423}}; a certain one, i.e. so-and-so; certain.

h6423.definition: from {{h6395}}; such a one, i.e. a specified person; such.

h6424.definition: a primitive root; properly, to roll flat, i.e. prepare (a road); also to revolve, i.e. weigh (mentally); make, ponder, weigh.

h6426.definition: a primitive root; properly, perhaps to rend, i.e. (by implication) to quiver; tremble.

h6428.definition: a primitive root; to roll (in dust); roll (wallow) self.

h6429.definition: from {{h6428}}; rolling, i.e. migratory; Pelesheth, a region of Syria; Palestina, Palestine, Philistia, Philistines.

h6430.definition: patrial from {{h6429}}; a Pelishtite or inhabitant of Pelesheth; Philistine.

h6431.definition: from an unused root meaning to flee; swiftness; Peleth, the name of two Israelites; Peleth.

h6432.definition: from the same form as {{h6431}}; a courier (collectively) or official messenger; Pelethites.

h6433.definition: (Aramaic) probably for {{h6310}}; the mouth (literally or figuratively); mouth.

h6434.definition: from an unused root meaning to turn; an angle (of a street or wall); corner.

h6435.definition: from {{h6437}}; properly, removal; used only (in the construction) adverb as conjunction, lest; (lest) (peradventure), that...not.

h6436.definition: of uncertain derivation; probably pastry; Pannag.

h6437.definition: a primitive root; to turn; by implication, to face, i.e. appear, look, etc.; appear, at (even-) tide, behold, cast out, come on, × corner, dawning, empty, go away, lie, look, mark, pass away, prepare, regard, (have) respect (to), (re-) turn (aside, away, back, face, self), × right (early).

h6438.definition: feminine of {{h6434}}; an angle; by implication, a pinnacle; figuratively, a chieftain; bulwark, chief, corner, stay, tower.

h6439.definition: or (more properly,) פְּנִיאֵל; from {{h6437}} and {{h410}}; face of God; Penuel or Peniel, a place East of Jordan; also (as Penuel) the name of two Israelites; Peniel, Penuel.

h6440.definition: plural (but always as singular) of an unused noun פָּנֶה; from {{h6437}}); the face (as the part that turns); used in a great variety of applications (literally and figuratively); also (with prepositional prefix) as a preposition (before, etc.); accept, a-(be-) fore(-time), against, anger, × as (long as), at,   battle,   because (of),   beseech, countenance, edge,   employ, endure,   enquire, face, favour, fear of, for, forefront(-part), form(-er time, -ward), from, front, heaviness, × him(-self),   honourable,   impudent,   in, it, look(-eth) (-s), × me,   meet, × more than, mouth, of, off, (of) old (time), × on, open,   out of, over against, the partial, person,   please, presence, propect, was purposed, by reason of,   regard, right forth,   serve, × shewbread, sight, state, straight,   street, × thee, × them(-selves), through (  -out), till, time(-s) past, (un-) to(-ward),   upon, upside (  down), with(-in,   -stand), × ye, × you.

h6441.definition: from {{h6440}} with directive enclitic; faceward, i.e. indoors; (with-) in(-ner part, -ward).

h6443.definition: or פָּנִי; from the same as {{h6434}}; probably a pearl (as round); ruby.

h6444.definition: probably feminine from {{h6443}} contr.; Peninnah, an Israelitess; Peninnah.

h6445.definition: a primitive root; to enervate; bring up.

h6446.definition: from {{h6461}}; properly, the palm (of the hand) or sole (of the foot) (compare {{h6447}}); by implication (plural); a long and sleeved tunic (perhaps simply a wide one; from the original sense of the root, i.e. of many breadths); (divers) colours.

h6447.definition: (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h6461}}; the palm (of the hand, as being spread out); participle

h6448.definition: a primitive root; to cut up, i.e. (figuratively) contemplate; consider.

h6449.definition: from {{h6448}}; a cleft; Pisgah, a Mountain East of Jordan; Pisgah.

h6450.definition: from {{h6446}} and the plural of {{h1818}}; palm (i.e. dell) of bloodshed; Pas-Dammim, a place in Palestine; Pas-dammim. Compare {{h658}}.

h6452.definition: a primitive root; to hop, i.e. (figuratively) skip over (or spare); by implication, to hesitate; also (literally) to limp, to dance; halt, become lame, leap, pass over.

h6453.definition: from {{h6452}}; a pretermission, i.e. exemption; used only techically of the Jewish Passover (the festival or the victim); passover (offering).

h6454.definition: from {{h6452}}; limping; Paseach, the name of two Israelites; Paseah, Phaseah.

h6456.definition: from {{h6458}}; an idol; carved (graven) image, quarry.

h6457.definition: from an unused root meaning to divide; divider; Pasak, an Israelite; Pasach.

h6458.definition: a primitive root; to carve, whether wood or stone; grave, hew.

h6460.definition: (Aramaic) or פְּסַנְתֵּרִין; a transliteration of the Greek,; psalterion; a lyre; psaltery.

h6461.definition: a primitive root; probably to disperse, i.e. (intransitive) disappear; cease.

h6462.definition: perhaps from {{h6461}}; dispersion; Pispah, an Israelite; Pispah.

h6463.definition: a primitive root; to scream; cry.

h6464.definition: or פָּעִי; from {{h6463}}; screaming; Pau or Pai, a place in Edom; Pai, Pau.

h6465.definition: from {{h6473}}; a gap; also {{h1187}}); Peör, a mountain East of Jordan; Baal Peor,	(for a deity worshipped there; Peor. See also {{h1047}}.

h6466.definition: a primitive root; to do or make (systematically and habitually), especially to practise; commit, (evil-) do(-er), make(-r), ordain, work(-er).

h6467.definition: from {{h6466}}; an act or work (concretely); act, deed, do, getting, maker, work.

h6468.definition: feminine passive participle of {{h6466}}; (abstractly) work; labour, reward, wages, work.

h6469.definition: from {{h6468}}; laborious; Peullethai, an Israelite; Peulthai.

h6470.definition: a primitive root; to tap, i.e. beat regularly; hence (generally) to impel or agitate; move, trouble.

h6471.definition: or (feminine) פַּעֲמָה; from {{h6470}}; a stroke, literally or figuratively (in various applications, as follow); anvil, corner, foot(-step), going, (hundred-) fold, × now, (this)   once, order, rank, step,   thrice, (often-), second, this, two) time(-s), twice, wheel.

h6473.definition: a primitive root; to yawn, i.e. open wide (literally or figuratively); gape, open (wide).

h6474.definition: from {{h6473}}; yawning; Paarai, an Israelite; Paarai.

h6475.definition: a primitive root; to rend, i.e. open (especially the mouth); deliver, gape, open, rid, utter.

h6476.definition: a primitive root; to break out (in joyful sound); break (forth, forth into joy), make a loud noise.

h6478.definition: a primitive root; to peel; pill.

h6480.definition: a primitive root; to rend (by earthquake); break.

h6481.definition: a primitive root; to split, i.e. wound; wound.

h6483.definition: from an unused root meaning to dissever; dispersive; Pitstsets, a priest; Apses (including the article).

h6484.definition: a primitive root; to peck at, i.e. (figuratively) stun or dull; press, urge, stubbornness.

h6485.definition: a primitive root; to visit (with friendly or hostile intent); by analogy, to oversee, muster, charge, care for, miss, deposit, etc.; appoint, × at all, avenge, bestow, (appoint to have the, give a) charge, commit, count, deliver to keep, be empty, enjoin, go see, hurt, do judgment, lack, lay up, look, make, × by any means, miss, number, officer, (make) overseer, have (the) oversight, punish, reckon, (call to) remember(-brance), set (over), sum, × surely, visit, want.

h6486.definition: feminine passive participle of {{h6485}}; visitation (in many senses, chiefly official); account, (that have the) charge, custody, that which...laid up, numbers, office(-r), ordering, oversight,   prison, reckoning, visitation.

h6487.definition: from {{h6485}}; a deposit; that which was delivered (to keep), store.

h6489.definition: from {{h6485}}; punishment; Pekod, a symbolic name for Babylon; Pekod.

h6490.definition: or פִּקֻּד; from {{h6485}}; properly, appointed, i.e. a mandate (of God; plural only, collectively, for the Law); commandment, precept, statute.

h6491.definition: a primitive root; to open (the senses, especially the eyes); figuratively, to be observant; open.

h6492.definition: from {{h6491}}; watch; Pekach, an Israelite king; Pekah.

h6493.definition: from {{h6491}}; clear-sighted; figuratively, intelligent; seeing, wise.

h6494.definition: from {{h6491}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has observed; Pekachjah, an Israelite king; Pekahiah.

h6495.definition: from {{h6491}} redoubled; opening (of a dungeon), i.e. jail-delivery (figuratively, salvation for sin); opening of the prison.

h6496.definition: from {{h6485}}; a superintendent (civil, military or religious); which had the charge, governor, office, overseer, (that) was set.

h6497.definition: from an unused root meaning to burst; only used as an architectural term of an ornament similar to {{h6498}},; a semi-globe; knop.

h6498.definition: from the same as {{h6497}}; the wild cucumber (from splitting open to shed its seeds); gourd.

h6499.definition: or פָּר; from {{h6565}}; a bullock (apparently as breaking forth in wild strength, or perhaps as dividing the hoof); (  young) bull(-ock), calf, ox.

h6500.definition: a primitive root; to bear fruit; be fruitful.
